-- Cameron Says to Extend Olympic Sports Funding to 2016 Rio Games
-- B y   R o b e r t   H u t t o n
-- 2012-08-12T08:18:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-12/cameron-says-to-extend-olympic-sports-funding-to-2016-rio-games.html
U.K. Prime Minister  David Cameron 
said government funding of elite sports will continue at a level
of 125 million pounds ($196 million) a year until the Rio
Olympic Games in 2016.  Cameron told the BBC the U.K.’s performance during the
London games over the past two weeks had “lifted the whole
country.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Hutton in London at 
